The '''[[1995 NFL season|1995]] [[Denver Broncos]] season''' was the team's 36th year in professional football and its 26th with the [[National Football League]]. The season would be noted for being the first year that Mike Shanahan was head coach. A turning point for the franchise would include the drafting of future Super Bowl Most Valuable Player Terrell Davis.
